    "recap_headline": "TCU",
    "recap_text": "TEMPE, Ariz.\n\u2013 A nine-run third inning helped Arizona State even the series as it handed No. 17 TCU a 15-8 loss Saturday night at Phoenix Municipal Stadium.\nLucas Franco\nhad a career-high four hits in the game.\nThe Rundown\nTCU took an early 1-0 lead in the second inning.\nBrady Dallimore\nled off the inning with a base hit and scored on a two-out\nLucas Franco\nsingle.\nThe Sun Devils sent 12 men to the plate in the third and scored nine times to break the game open. With one out, seven straight batters reached as ASU built a 5-1 lead. The big blow in the inning was a two-out grand slam.\nTCU didn't go quietly, pushing across five runs in the top of the fourth. The first seven batters in the inning reached.\nJack Arthur\ndrove in the first run of the frame.\nRob Liddington\nlined a bases-loaded single into left for two more runs.\nSawyer Strosnider\nworked a bases-loaded walk forcing a pitching change. The reliever did his job, getting a double play and a ground out to end the inning.\nArizona State got an unearned run back in the fourth and added three more runs in the sixth on a pair of home runs. Another miscue in the seventh extended the Sun Devil lead to 14-6.\nJack Bell\nled off the eighth with his first home run of the season and\nSawyer Strosnider\ndrove in a two-out run to make it a 14-8. ASU's final run came on a sacrifice fly in the eighth.\nLance Davis\n(0-3) took the loss after allowing six runs on eight hits in 2 1/3 innings.\nStat of the Game:\n9 \u2013\nArizona State scored nine times in the third.\nNotes:\n\u2022 TCU homered in a game for the 13\nth\ntime this season.\n\u2022 TCU was outhit by its opponent for the 10\nth\ntime this season.\n\u2022 TCU scored first in a game for the 11\nth\ntime this season.\n\u2022\nColton Griffin\nhas reached safely in nine straight games.\n\u2022\nSawyer Strosnider\nhas reached safely in 34 straight games dating back to last season.\n\u2022 Strosnider tallied his fifth multi-RBI game of the season and the 18\nth\nof his career.\n\u2022\nNolan Traeger\nhas reached safely in 12 straight games.\n\u2022\nJack Bell\nhit his first home run of the season and the seventh of his career.\n\u2022\nRob Liddington\nhas reached safely in 10 straight games.\n\u2022 Liddington collected his third multi-RBI game of the year and the 21\nst\nof his career.\n\u2022\nLucas Franco\nrecorded his fourth career multi-hit game.\nNext Up:\nWith the loss, TCU falls to 11-7 on the season and 1-1 in Big 12 play.\u00a0The rubber match of the series is set for Sunday afternoon at 3 p.m. (CT).\nTrever Baumler\nwill get the start for the Frogs. The contest will be televised on ESPN+."
